# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Count the modulo with value of all the elements
`For Negative` : make its counterpositive then add its modulo 
`ie` : `(x % value) + value`
`For Positive` : `x % value`
Now if modulo is 2 and your value is 5 then you can either make 2 , 7 , 12 .. and so on that means you can make `5*k + 2` `k >=0`

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(n)`
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: `O(value)`
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findSmallestInteger(vector<int>& v, int value) {
        unordered_map<int,int> moduloCounter;
        for(int x : v) {
            moduloCounter[((x % value) + value) % value] += 1;
        }
        for(int i = 0; i <= v.size(); i += 1) {
            int rem = i % value;
            if(moduloCounter.count(rem) && moduloCounter[rem] > 0) moduloCounter[rem] -= 1;
            else return i;

        }
        return 0;
    }
};
```

