# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We can convert any value to its modulus with value.So i will just count nums[i]%value in a hashmap and check from 0 til n-1.As we know MEX value can be maximum N. SO answer will be between [0,N].
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Initialise a pre vector of size N with value 0 to check MEX,And a ordered map of <int,int>.
2. Traverse through the array nums.if element is negative then add x*value to make it positive 
3. Take nums[i]%value and store in map.
4. Traverse again in for loop from i=0 till i=n-1.Check mp[index%value] is gretaer then 0 or not is it is fill the pre[i] as 1.and decrease map vaue by 1.
5. Initialise ans as n, Check in pre array if any element is 0 then return its index.Otherwise return ans at the end.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N*LOG(N))
