# Intuition
Can you convert a number X to a number Y ? 
Yes, the condition is the value you can add/subtract any number of times (let’s say val) satisfies the equation 
(X-Y)%val=0.
# Approach


Assuming 3 is the value and you’ve got v=[1,3,5,6] as the numbers. Taking mod of each number with val(3) we get v\`=[1,0,2,0]. What’s the MEX? It’s 4 actually. But how? You can use construct 0 from v\`[1], 1 from v\`[0], 2 from v\`[2], 3 from v\`[3]. You can’t construct 4 now!
To formalize we can say that we can convert a number X to Y (according to our explanation above (X&Y). so we need to check if we have an element i%val in the array v`. But when you utilize an element for construction you need to make sure that It’s not utilized again and hence you need to decrement it’s frequency [use hashmaps for this purpose]. The code is simple and self-explanatory.
You are requested to go through the video here for more clarity:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6gf3ijbYWrs


