# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Convert the given array to module array in the following ways:----
**array = [4,2,-5,8,-9,10] value = 4**

if **array[i]>0, then array[i] = array[i] % value**
else **array[i] = value + array[i] % value**

**Now the array becomes = [0,2,3,0,3,2]**
Now we see that we can handle **all cases of Array[i]+n*Value(here n = 0,1,2,3......)** .

**For example:-
Array[0]=0: 0,4,8,12,16....... We can choose one position among them but we choose minimum (0) first.
Table[1]=2: 2,6,10,14,18,... We can choose one position among them but we choose minimum(2) first.
Array[2]=3: 3,7,11,15,19,... We can choose one position among them but we choose minimum(3) first.
array[3]=0: 0,4,8,12,16.......we can choose one position among them but we choose minimum first (4 because 0 is already taken) .
Table[4]=3: 3,7,11,15,19,... We can choose one position among them but we choose the minimum first (7 because 3 is already taken).
Table[1]=2: 2,6,10,14,18,... We can choose a position among them but we choose the minimum first (6 because 2 is already taken).**


