# Approach
This code finds the smallest integer not present in the given array nums by using a map to count the occurrences of each remainder value when dividing the elements by value. It then iterates through the array to find the smallest integer that is not present in the array based on the remainder values.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int findSmallestInteger(int[] nums, int value) {

        int max = 0;
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
 // Count the occurrences of each remainder value when divided by 'value'

        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            int key = nums[i]%value;
            if(key<0){
                key = key+value;
            }
           map.put(key, map.getOrDefault(key,0)+1);
        }
 // Check for the smallest integer not present in the array
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            int num = i;
            if(map.containsKey(i)){
               while(map.get(i)>1){
                 num +=value;
                 map.put(num,map.getOrDefault(num,0)+1);
                 map.put(i,map.get(i)-1);
               }
            }else return i;
        }

        return nums.length;

    }
}
```

