##### Intuition
Count the modulo with value of all the elements
**For Negative :** make its counterpositive then add its modulo
ie : **(x % value) + value**
Now if number is 7 and your value is 5 then you can either make 2 , 7 , 12 .. and so on that means you can make **5 * k + 2** where **(k >= 0)**

* Time complexity: **O(n)**
* Space complexity: **O(value)**

##### Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findSmallestInteger(vector<int>& nums, int value) {
        vector<int> freq(value);
        for(int num : nums)
            freq[((num % value) + value) % value]++;
        int mn_pos = min_element(freq.begin(), freq.end()) - freq.begin();
        return freq[mn_pos] * value + mn_pos;        
    }
};
