# Intuition
First calculate the number of all remainders for items of array nums by dividing by value.

# Approach
First calculate the number of all remainders with method
```
private int[] CreateSet(int[] nums, int value)
```
Then find the first index with minimum number of remainders.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int FindSmallestInteger(int[] nums, int value) {
        var arr = CreateSet(nums, value);
        var minIndex = 0;
        var min = arr[minIndex];
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.Length; i++)
        {
            if (arr[minIndex] > arr[i])
            {
                minIndex = i;
            }
        }
        var rs = minIndex + arr[minIndex] * value;
        return rs;
    }
    private int[] CreateSet(int[] nums, int value)
    {
        var rs = new int[value];
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.Length; i++)
        {
            var index = nums[i] % value;
            if (index < 0) index += value;
            rs[index]++;
        }
        return rs;
    }
}
```

