# Intuition
First we sort the array , then we store the frequency of all the numbers in the array .
then we started looking for non-negative integers starting from 0.
We named the variable ans , for which we are looking for

if the ans founds in array then increment it , if not then find someone in map that can make ans by adding of substracting value .

//steps are explained in comments

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n Log n)

- Space complexity:O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findSmallestInteger(vector<int>& nums, int value) {
        int n=nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());

        unordered_map<int,int> cnt;
        for(auto x:nums)    cnt[x]++;   //count frequency of all the numbers

        int ans=0, i=0;
        while(i<n && nums[i]<ans)  i++; //find first non negative number
        while(1){
            if(i<n && nums[i]==ans 
                    && cnt[nums[i]]>0){  //ans is the number we are looking for
                cnt[nums[i]]--;          //decrease its frequency as it can't be use again
                ans++;                   //now we had to look for next no
                i++;                     //from next index    
            }
            else {
                bool found=false;
                for(auto &[no,freq]:cnt){
                    if( (ans-no)%value==0 && freq>0 ){
                        cnt[no]--;
                        ans++;
                        found=true;
                    }
                }
                if(!found)  return ans;     //if a number not found after all map iteration then its the answer
            }
        }
        return INT_MAX;                     //control never reach here
    }
};
```
