Count $${num}\mod{value}$$.
For MEX from 0 to n-1, check if $${MEX}\mod{value}$$ is still available in  count. 
If out of stock, return the current MEX.
If everything match, return n.

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def findSmallestInteger(self, nums: List[int], value: int) -> int:
        ct = Counter([x % value for x in nums])
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            x = i % value
            if ct[x]:
                ct[x] -= 1
            else:
                return i
        return len(nums)
